Privacy Policy

Last updated: 02/03/2026

1. Transparency & Open Source

DeltaBotz is an open-source project.
The source code that governs data handling can be reviewed publicly at:
https://github.com/bshar1865/DeltaBotz

This allows users to verify what data is collected and how it is used.

2. Data We Collect

The Bot may collect only the minimum data necessary for functionality, including:

Discord User IDs

Discord Server (Guild) IDs

Channel IDs

Configuration settings

Command usage metadata

Message content is not collected or stored, unless explicitly required for a specific feature (e.g. moderation or logging).

3. Purpose of Data Collection

Data is used solely to:

Provide core bot functionality

Store user or server preferences

Prevent abuse

Improve reliability and performance

4. Data Storage & Security

Data is stored securely with restricted access

Reasonable safeguards are used to protect stored information

Absolute security cannot be guaranteed

5. Data Sharing

We do not sell, trade, or monetize user data.

Data may only be disclosed:

If legally required

To enforce these Terms

To protect users, servers, or the Bot’s integrity

6. Data Retention & Deletion

Data is retained only as long as necessary

Server-specific data may be removed when the Bot is removed from a server

Users may request deletion of their data where technically feasible

7. User Rights

You may request:

Confirmation of stored data

Data correction or deletion

Requests can be made via:
[EMAIL / SUPPORT SERVER]

8. Third-Party Services

The Bot operates within Discord and is subject to Discord’s own Privacy Policy. We are not responsible for Discord’s data practices.

9. Changes to This Policy

This Privacy Policy may be updated periodically. Continued use of the Bot indicates acceptance of the revised policy.

10. Contact

For privacy-related inquiries:
[EMAIL / DISCORD TAG / SUPPORT SERVER]
